Rep. Giffords to attend shuttle Endeavor launch next month
HOUSTON — Rep. Gabrielle Giffords (D-Ariz.) plans to attend the launch of the space shuttle Endeavor on April 19, Fox News Channel confirmed Thursday.
Giffords’ husband, astronaut Mark Kelly, will pilot the final mission of the NASA shuttle.
The wounded congresswoman continues to recover at a Texas rehabilitation facility after she was shot in the head during an alleged assassination attempt in Tucson, Ariz., in January.